<br>
1) Go back to the way it was before, all (P) clerics now and in the future able to switch. I see no support for this at all.<br>
<br>
2) What we've got now, remove any possibility of corruption by selling spots with a rule stating that no one is allowed to switch at all, except in the case of the one (P) cleric on top letting the one directly behind him or her go because they arent able to camp Rage yet because of RL. That's what I happen to believe is most fair, and so far, I perceive this as being what most of the server wants.<br>
<br>
3) Compromise between the two, by drawing a line that all future clerics cant switch. Perhaps also setting a one-switch limit for each (P) person. (Though this would complicate the rules a bit) There is some support for this.<br>
<br>
At the moment, we are going with #2, because that's what the majority appears to want. So far, it looks like with few exceptions, the only ones advocating #3 are those with a personal stake in being able to switch, leaping over lots of other clerics and weeks of time. Not surprisingly, those with no plans of switching dont appear to like that idea at all. If you have an opinion at all on this, please feel free to speak up if you havent already! As they say in politics, if you dont vote, then you really have no reason to complain about who wins the election. <p>Cayleu Starshine
